  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorism Financing Act (Australia)\n\n3. Key Compliance Requirements:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Record-keeping regulations\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- License revocation for financial institutions\n\n5. Key Regulatory Focus Areas:\n- Financial institutions\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate transactions\n- International wire transfers\n- Cash-intensive businesses\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and reporting mechanisms.",
